                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Upper margin: 1.9 cm. Left margin: 2.5 cm. Letter-height  averages 2 mm. A single hand has written the text in black ink. It is small, upright uncial with ornamental serifs, very regular. Two prominent features of the hand are the three-bar alpha and a curved epsilon which has its tongue drawn in a separate stroke. Note the diple-periestgmene attached to 388, the word substitution at 385, and the form-substitution at 389</p>
